PD Reporter @PeopleDailyKe Nakuru Senator Susan Kihika has urged parliamentarians to ensure that innovation in science and technology advances gender equality and the empowerment of women and girls. Speaking during the opening session of the 139th Assembly of the Inter-parliamentary Union (IPU) in Geneva, Switzerland, Kihika impressed on the importance of ensuring women and girls thrive in the technology sector. “As parliamentarians, we have to adapt to change and ensure technological progress impacts positively on women and girls,” said Kihika, who is also the president of the Forum for Women Parliamentarians.